8 Bit NES cover of the title theme from Kirby's Return to Dream Land. What a jaunty tune.

I use Logic Pro 9 and "chipsounds", by Plogue, in all my 8 Bit works, and Kontakt 5 and soundfonts available online for all my other retro remixes.

Feel free to use any of my remixes for your own YouTube videos, just leave a link to my channel in the video description. \(｀_´)/

======

I make all my retro remixes from scratch, it is a creative process in which I rework or re-imagine existing tracks into an retro inspired sound. Proof of creation will always be available if needed.

snippet.title: Castlevania: Haunted Castle - Cross Your Heart (8-bit NES remix)
snippet.description:
Made from scratch. I transcribed the song by ear, and optimized it to sound best within the NES' stock limitations (meaning no addition sound chip expansions). I had to take some slight liberties with backing melodies to get the most out of the song, but I think it was for the best, and I'm happy with the result. One thing of note is that I used Mega Man style synth drums (using a downward sliding triangle wave) , and am unaware if any Castlevania songs used this. I just felt like using it to give the toms more "depth".

Made in "FL Studio 8" using the "Universal NES Soundfont".

snippet.title: Original - Sunsoft Style Boss
snippet.description:
http://www.mediafire.com/?edojtqlqc0qprf8
50 videos! Yayyeah!
I'm a big fan of the NES music that was produced by game developer Sunsoft's music crew. I've always particularly enjoyed their boss themes. This is my attempt at making a boss theme that sounds somewhat like a Sunsoft track, made using Famitracker. My chief influences were Journey to Silius and Ufouria (hence the pictures).
I was going for a sort of rock-style track (as you can probably hear in one of the melodies). I'm also quite happy with how the run section at the end turned out since that's pretty much the first time I've attempted anything as complex as that.

Also it's really late to say this (I've gained 11 subscribers since) but thank you all for getting me to 100 subscribers! It's truly appreciated.

Sorry it took so long to finally make this song, I've had a lot of things to deal with these past few weeks that have been giving me some stress; I can't focus when I'm stressed, so I had to keep putting it off. snippet.title: Super Mario RPG - Armed Boss Battle Famitracker Cover (8-bit)
snippet.description:
Game and all contents are copyright to Squaresoft / Nintendo

Composed in famitracker 0.3.7

Thanks to coatlesscarl and NecrophageonIII for sharing their instruments with me - the hat came from coatlesscarl's cover of 'the extreme', and the snare was featured in NecrophageonIII's original track 'adrenal daydream'

I've learned an awful lot about famitracker, and composing in general since I started working with the software a few months ago. However, it's pretty easy to tell that armed boss battle was my first ever public release.

I went over it with a fine tooth comb, and applied everything i've learned since I began. I'm pretty happy with the end result, and it's much more accurate all around.

snippet.title: (8-Bit NES) Sky Station Galaxy + Super Mario Galaxy 2 Theme
snippet.description:
This was one of the covers  I submitted for Famicompo Mini Vol. 8.  I placed 4th in the covers section (and another two covers were submitted along with it).  I am going to do some updates to the other two covers before I put them up onto YouTube.

This one is an RP2A03 only cover of both Sky Station Galaxy and the Super Mario Galaxy 2 Theme,  after the second loop of Sky Station Galaxy, it transitions into the second half of the Super Mario Galaxy 2 Theme and eventually loops back to Sky Station Galaxy.  Unfortunately when I submit the timings for Famicompo I incorrectly specified a shorter time for this song, so if you grabbed the MP3 renders before you will have missed the ending!
